'''Tindel Marchant''' is an [[NPC]] involved in the quest [[One Small Favour]], where he provides [[iron oxide]] in exchange for a mattress. He is located on the southern dock in [[Port Khazard]]. Having him identify a [[rusty sword]] is a requirement for the [[Easy Ardougne Diary]].

==Repairs==
Tindel can repair degradable [[armour]]s such as [[Barrows equipment]] for the player at a price. The equipment does not need to be fully degraded in order to have it repaired. The cost of any repair is proportional to how degraded the item is. Alternatively, players can repair the armours at a cheaper price themselves at an [[armour stand]] in any [[player-owned house]].

===Rusty equipment===
He will restore [[rusty sword]]s and [[rusty scimitar]]s for 100 gp each. They will randomly be repaired into [[sword]]s or [[scimitar]]s, ranging from [[bronze weapons|bronze]] to [[mithril weapons|mithril]]. Sometimes he returns around 2000 [[coins]] instead of a fixed weapon, saying that the item was an ancient artefact he added to his collection.

===Barrows equipment===
The cost for [[Barrows equipment]] depends on the equipment slot that the item is worn in. When fully degraded, Tindel's repair cost is as follows:
